e": "iso3901.isrc.ISRC.agency", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "iso3901.isrc.ISRC.stringify", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "separator", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Print ISRC as string\n\nParameters\n----------\nseparator : bool, optional\n    Whether hyphen should be inserted between segments. Defaults to True.\n    If hyphenation is not intended, it is much simpler to call `str()`\n    on the object.\n\nReturns\n-------\nstr\n    Resulting ISRC string"]}, {"name": "iso3901.isrc.ISRC._parse", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "_raw", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "iso3901.isrc.ISRC.parse", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": {"name": "Type", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Type", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "ISRC", "xref": {"fqname": "iso3901.isrc.ISRC", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "_raw", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "ISRC", "xref": {"fqname": "iso3901.isrc.ISRC", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Parses ISRC string into structure\n\nIt checks for `CCOOOYYNNNNN` or `CC-OOO-YY-NNNNN` pattern\nas mandated by ISRC Handbook, optionally prefixed with \"ISRC \".\nAny trailing text is ignored.\n\nSince `0.3.0`, it also determines if country code belongs to\nnewest published prefixes by IFPI. If this check is undesirable,\nconstruct ISRC object directly instead of using this method.\n\n# Note\n\nThis package will *never* check if ISRC string is used in\nsome sort of document as illustration purpose (and\ntherefore known invalid codes). Collecting those codes is\nimpractical.\n\n# Parameters\n\n\\_raw\n\n: The ISRC string to be validated and parsed\n\n# Raises\n\nTypeError\n\n: If supplied argument is not a string\n\nValueError\n\n: If ISRC segments do not conform to standard\n\n# Returns\n\nISRC\n\n: The structured object representing ISRC data\n"]}, {"name": "iso3901.isrc.ISRC.validate", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "_raw", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Validates if supplied ISRC string is parseable.\n\nIt is almost the same as `parse()` method, but instead of returning\nthe `ISRC` object, `validate()` only determines if it is parseable.\n\n# See Also\n\n- `parse()` method for more detail\n\n# Parameters\n\n\\_raw\n\n: The string to be validated\n\n# Returns\n\nbool\n\n: Whether string is plausible ISRC code\n"]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "iso3901.isrc.ISRC.owner", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "iso3901.isrc.ISRC.year", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "iso3901.isrc.ISRC.designation", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "iso3901.isrc.ISRC.raw", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Objectified ISRC structure defined in ISO 3901:2019\n\n# Attributes\n\nowner\n\n: 5-character registrant code of issuer of ISRC, with first 2 letters\n  strictly alphabetic and remaining alphanumeric\n\nyear\n\n: last 2 digit of reference year (usually means recording year)\n\ndesignation\n\n: 5-digit identifier for recording, unique within above reference year.\n\nraw\n\n: If ISRC is parsed via `parse` method, this attribute preserves the\n  original string.\n\nprefix\n\n: First 2 letters of ISRC string. See `country` property below.\n\ncountry\n\n: Read-only property corresponding to country represented by first\n  2 letter of ISRC. This is most likely the same as ISO 3166 2-letter\n  country code, but there are exceptions. The property could be None\n  if ISRC object is manually created with illegal prefix\n  (not via `.parse()` method).\n\nagency\n\n: Read-only property corresponding to national (or international)\n  ISRC allocation agency. Like the `country` property above, this property\n  can be None if ISRC object contains illegal prefix.\n", "fmt: on"]}], "exports": [{"name": "iso3901.isrc.Agency", "xref": {"fqname": "iso3901.isrc.Agency", "project": null}}, {"name": "iso3901.isrc.Allocation", "xref": {"fqname": "iso3901.isrc.Allocation", "project": null}}, {"name": "iso3901.isrc.ISRC", "xref": {"fqname": "iso3901.isrc.ISRC", "project": null}}]}]}